quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  3,52,"And when Jesus perceived their unbelief, He said, 'Who are my helpers for God?' Said the apostles, 'We are God's helpers. We believe in God, so bear witness that we are resigned"
  3,53,"Lord, we have believed in what Thou hast revealed, and we have followed the Apostle, so write us down with those which bear witness"
  3,54,"But they (the Jews) were crafty, and God was crafty, for God is the best of crafty ones"
  3,55,"When God said, 'O Jesus! I will make Thee die and take Thee up again to me and will clear thee of those who misbelieve, and will make those who follow thee above those who misbelieve, at the day of judgment, then to me is your return. I will decide between you concerning that wherein ye disagree"
  3,56,"And as for those who misbelieve, I will punish them with grievous punishment in this world and the next, and they shall have none to help them"
  3,57,"But as for those who believe and do what is right, He will pay them their reward, for God loves not the unjust"
  3,58,That is what we recite to thee of the signs and of the wise reminder
  3,59,"Verily the likeness of Jesus with God is as the likeness of Adam. He created him from earth, then He said to him BE, and he was"
  3,60,"the truth from thy Lord, so be thou not of those who are in doubt"
  3,61,"And whoso disputeth with thee after what has come to thee of knowledge, say, 'Come, let us call our sons and your sons, and our women and your women, and ourselves and yourselves: then we will imprecate and put God's curse on those who lie"
  3,62,"Verily, those are the true stories, and there is no god but God, and, verily, God He is the mighty, the wise"
  3,63,"but if they turn back, God knows the evildoers"
  3,64,"Say, 'O ye people of the Book, come to a word laid down plainly between us and you, that we will not serve other than God, nor associate aught with him, nor take each other for lords rather than God.' But if they turn back then say, 'Bear witness that we are resigned"
  3,65,"O people of the Book, why do ye dispute about Abraham, when the law and the gospel were not revealed until after him? What! do ye not understand"
  3,66,"Here ye are, disputing about what ye have some knowledge of; why then do ye dispute about what ye have no knowledge of? God knows and ye know not"
  3,67,"Abraham was not a Jew, nor yet a Christian, but he was a `Hanif resigned, and not of the idolaters"
  3,68,"Verily, the people most worthy of Abraham are those who follow him and his prophets, and those who believe;- God is the patron of the believers"
  3,69,"A sect of the people of the Book would fain they could lead you astray, but they only lead themselves astray, and they do not perceive"
  3,70,"O people of the Book! why do ye disbelieve in the signs of God, the while ye witness them"
  3,71,O people of the Book! why do ye clothe the truth with falsehood and hide the truth the while ye know
  3,72,"A sect of the people of the Book say, 'Believe in what was revealed to those who believed at the first appearance of the day, and disbelieve it at the end thereof,' - that (others) may perchance go back (from their faith)"
  3,73,"do not believe save one who followeth your religion.' Say, 'Verily, the (true) guidance is the guidance of God, that one should be given like what ye are given.' Or would they dispute with you before your Lord, say, 'Grace is in the hand of God, He gives it to whom he pleases, for God both comprehends and knows"
  3,74,"He specially favours with his mercy whom he pleases, for God is Lord of mighty grace"